.TH FILENAME-SLUGGER 1 "2026-06-03" "1.0.0" "Zensical Documentation Skills"
.SH NAME
filename-slugger \- convert Chinese filenames to English kebab-case and update references
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B filename-slugger
.I command
.RB [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B filename-slugger
converts Chinese-named Zensical documentation files (.md) to English
kebab-case filenames, automatically updating all internal references.
.PP
Zensical auto-generates URL slugs from filenames. Chinese filenames produce
URL-encoded, unreadable slugs. English kebab-case filenames produce clean,
readable, SEO-friendly URLs. However, renaming files without updating
cross-references will break wikilinks, markdown links, navigation entries,
and frontmatter permalinks. This script handles all of that.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B rename
Rename a single file and update all references. This is the primary
command. It renames the file on disk and searches the entire project
for wikilinks ([[old-name]]), markdown links (](old-name.md)),
zensical.toml nav paths, and the file's own permalink frontmatter.
.TP
.B check
Dry-run mode. Preview all changes that would be made without modifying
any files. Always run this before rename to verify the changes.
.TP
.B scan
List all Chinese-named .md files in the project. Shows each file's
relative path and whether it has a permalink set. Useful for discovery
before deciding which files to convert.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-dry\-run, \-n
Preview all changes without modifying any files.
.TP
.B \-\-verbose, \-v
Show detailed progress for each reference being updated.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-nav
Skip updating zensical.toml and zensical.en.toml nav paths.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-links
Skip updating wikilinks and markdown links. Only renames the file
and updates the frontmatter permalink.
.TP
.B \-\-force, \-f
Skip confirmation prompts. Useful in scripts or batch operations.
.TP
.B \-\-project\-root DIR
Explicit project root directory. Auto-detected if omitted by looking
for zensical.toml in parent directories of the old file path.
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
.I old-path
Path to the Chinese-named .md file, e.g.
.RI "docs/ec/orders/\"訂單出貨流程.md\"" .
.TP
.I new-name
Desired English kebab-case name. The .md extension is optional.
Example:
.RI "order-shipping-flow" .
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
filename-slugger scan
List all Chinese-named files in the project.
.TP
filename-slugger check docs/ec/orders/訂單出貨流程.md order-shipping-flow
Preview changes for renaming one file.
.TP
filename-slugger check docs/ec/orders/訂單出貨流程.md order-shipping-flow \-v
Same, with detailed reference breakdown.
.TP
filename-slugger rename docs/ec/orders/訂單出貨流程.md order-shipping-flow
Execute the rename with all reference updates.
.TP
filename-slugger rename docs/ec/orders/訂單出貨流程.md order-shipping-flow \-\-no-nav
Rename and update links, but skip zensical.toml nav updates.
.TP
python3 rename_slug.py rename docs/ec/products/設定商品自訂分類群組.md custom-product-groupings \-\-project\-root /path/to/project
Run with explicit project root.
.SH SLUG CONVENTION
Follow existing project patterns:
.PP
Correct:
.IP \(bu
All lowercase: order-shipping-flow
.IP \(bu
Kebab-case hyphens: edit-order-content
.IP \(bu
Start and end with letter/digit: cancel-order
.IP \(bu
Use standard terms: cvs, tcat, ecpay, b2c, c2c
.PP
Incorrect:
.IP \(bu
Underscores: order_shipping
.IP \(bu
CamelCase: orderShipping
.IP \(bu
Generic names: process, guide, flow
.SH FILES
.TP
.I scripts/rename_slug.py
Python script that performs the rename and reference updates.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR permalink\-generator (1),
.BR frontmatterer (1)
.SH NOTES
.PP
Man pages follow the same convention as all Zensical documentation skills.
Each skill stores its man page at
.IR <skill-path>/man/<skill-name>.1 .
Use
.BR man (1)
with the skill name to view a skill's documentation.
